        <p>The cuisine of South Asia is focused principally on the cuisines of the countries of Bangladesh, India, Pakistan, Srilanka, Maldives and Nepal. South-Asian cuisine is as rich and diverse as the country itself. The cuisine of South-Asian is influenced by the cultural and religious beliefs of many people in these country. Vegetarian dishes are often paired with curry causes that can be very spicy. South-Asian cuisine typically features different kinds of rice as well as beans and peas. Typical spices are cumin, chili, turmeric, coriander, and ginger. People familiar with South-Asian food will immediately recognize the characteristic spice combinations. Moreoever, south-asian cuisine is also based on dishes made from wheat and rice with different vegetables as well as lentils. The majority of dishes containing meat use chicken, lamb or sometimes mutton.</p></br>
